oc:kn_2ce2fb73 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing reference files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid deeply nested references. Keep references one level deep from SKILL.md. For reference files longer than 100 lines, include a table of contents at the top." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Deep nesting makes resources undiscoverable. A TOC lets Claude preview scope without loading the full file." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5fd9c7ed a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any new skill from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Understand the skill with concrete examples (gather usage patterns, triggers, user scenarios). 2. Plan reusable contents (identify scripts/references/assets needed). 3. Initialize the skill (run init_skill.py). 4. Edit the skill (implement resources, write SKILL.md). 5. Package the skill (run package_skill.py). 6. Iterate based on real usage." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_63c9cb83 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing SKILL.md frontmatter vs body" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never put 'when to use' information in the SKILL.md body. All triggering context belongs in the YAML frontmatter description field — the body is only loaded AFTER triggering." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Claude uses frontmatter to decide whether to trigger the skill. Body content is invisible during trigger evaluation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a21b65d5 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or editing any SKILL.md" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The context window is a shared, finite resource. Keep SKILL.md under 500 lines. Only include information Claude doesn't already know. Challenge each paragraph: 'Does this justify its token cost?'" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Skills share context with system prompt, conversation history, and other skill metadata. Bloat degrades all downstream performance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_a4e8507f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before running package_skill.py" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before packaging, ensure: YAML frontmatter has valid name and description, skill name is hyphen-case (lowercase, digits, hyphens, max 64 chars), description is under 1024 chars with no angle brackets." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The packaging script validates these rules and will refuse to package non-compliant skills." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b2d32cd0 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling skill directory contents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT create extraneous files (README.md, CHANGELOG.md, INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md, etc.). Only include SKILL.md, scripts/, references/, and assets/ — nothing else." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Extra files add clutter and confusion. Skills should contain only what an AI agent needs to do the job." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b4de681f a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding how to encode skill instructions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Match freedom level to task fragility: High freedom (text instructions) for flexible tasks; Medium freedom (pseudocode/scripts with params) when a preferred pattern exists; Low freedom (specific scripts, few params) for fragile, error-prone operations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-constraining flexible tasks wastes tokens; under-constraining fragile tasks invites errors." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c65f72cc a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing skill file structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use three-level progressive disclosure: (1) Metadata always in context (~100 words), (2) SKILL.md body loaded on trigger (<5k words), (3) Bundled resources loaded as needed by Claude." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Minimizes context consumption while making detailed information discoverable when actually needed." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f29c064e a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When distributing content across skill files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not duplicate information between SKILL.md and reference files. Information should live in one place. Prefer references for detailed material; keep only essential procedural instructions in SKILL.md." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Duplication wastes tokens and creates inconsistency when one copy is updated but not the other." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

